[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    281[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;191;97;106mThe Problem section is excellent. The folder vignette ("They put it on the passenger seat. They drive home.") is the kind of writing the style guide explicitly calls for, and the meta-observation ("Every step of this story is the system working as designed") sets up the technical framing without preaching.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    282[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m "This is a recommendation problem. It's a reasonably contained one, because the catalog is finite and curated. There's no risk of the recommender hallucinating a piece of content that doesn't exist; everything in the catalog has been clinically reviewed." Three sentences that tell the reader exactly what kind of problem they're being introduced to.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    283[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m "Curated vs. open catalog. The catalog is curated by clinical content teams. Every item has been reviewed. There are no fake reviews, no SEO gaming, no spam. [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThis is rare and lovely.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m" Best closing four-word sentence in the chapter.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    284[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m "The right approach is a small toolbox of well-understood techniques layered on top of each other, with the layering itself doing most of the work." Clean structural insight, in voice.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    285[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m "Why Not Just Use an LLM for Everything?" is the section the rest of the book has been waiting for. The four bullets (cost, latency, auditability, determinism) are crisp, and the punchline ("What LLMs are great for in this pipeline is content tailoring, not content selection") is exactly right.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    286[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m "Reading Level Is the Sleeper Feature" is one of the strongest sections in the book so far. "Relevance without comprehension is not relevance" deserves to be a chapter epigraph somewhere.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    287[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m "Multilingual Is Not Optional" lands. "If you don't have Spanish content for a topic, that's a content gap to flag back to the content team, not a feature for the model to optimize around" is the right answer to a question many recipes get wrong.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    288[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The Honest Take's three paragraphs are all earned: the content-ops underinvestment point, the LLM-is-rarely-the-answer point, and the explicit-preference-capture point. The closing point about UI framing ("'We recommend you read X' lands very differently from 'based on your recent visit, this might be helpful'") is patient-experience wisdom that engineers rarely articulate.[K
